description.plain:
Reneé Rapp (born on January 10, 2000) is an American actress and singer. In 2018, she won the Jimmy Award for Best Performance by an Actress. She currently plays Leighton in the HBO Max comedy series The Sex Lives of College Girls, for at least 2 seasons.

In 2022 she started to record her songs and the first piece called “Tattoos” was released on 3rd of June, 2022.
